p: In the District Court of the 3d Judicial District of Washington Territory holding Terms at Port Townsend
The President of the United States To James Eaves Greeting

We command you that you have the bodies Rosa Moulton and Nellie Moulton by you illegally detained as it is said, together with the cause of said detention, by what soever names said Rosa Moulton and Nellie Moulton shall be called before the Hon R.S. Greene Judge of of the above Entitled Court at the hour of half past one oclock P.M. of the 14th day of November 1883 at the Court house in Port Townsend, to do and receive what shall then and there be considered, concerning the same.
And have you there and then this writ
Judge of said District Court this 14th day of November 1883

p.unclear: Attesting here and the cause the day
